Note:
==============================================================================
AES-GCM - Galois/Counter Mode AEAD per NIST SP 800-38D
==============================================================================

This module implements the AES-GCM (Galois/Counter Mode) authenticated
encryption with associated data construction per NIST SP 800-38D. It supports
AES-128, AES-192, and AES-256 underlying block ciphers, with the canonical
96-bit IV per SP 800-38D section 8.2.1.

Algorithm:
  Let E_K(.) be the underlying AES block-encrypt function. Let H = E_K(0^128)
  be the hash subkey (encryption of the all-zeros block under K).

  For a 96-bit IV:
    J0 = IV || 0x00000001        (a 128-bit counter block)
  For non-96-bit IVs SP 800-38D specifies a GHASH-based derivation; we
  REJECT non-96-bit IVs in this implementation (see @Security_Scope on
  the misuse-resistance rationale).

  Encryption of plaintext P with associated data A:
    C = GCTR_K(inc32(J0), P)     (CTR-mode encrypt starting at J0+1)
    u = 128 * ceil(|C|/128) - |C|
    v = 128 * ceil(|A|/128) - |A|
    S = GHASH_H(A || 0^v || C || 0^u || [len(A)]_64 || [len(C)]_64)
    T = MSB_t(GCTR_K(J0, S))     (tag is GCTR encryption of S at counter J0)

  Decryption of ciphertext C with tag T':
    Recompute T from C, A, K, H, J0. If T != T' constant-time, reject.
    Else P = GCTR_K(inc32(J0), C).

  The 32-bit counter increments modulo 2^32 within the 128-bit block per
  SP 800-38D section 6.2.

GHASH:
  GHASH_H(X) operates on a sequence of 128-bit blocks X_1, X_2, ..., X_m.
    Y_0 = 0
    For i in 1..m: Y_i = (Y_{i-1} XOR X_i) * H        in GF(2^128)
    Output Y_m
  Multiplication in GF(2^128) uses the reduction polynomial
  R = x^128 + x^7 + x^2 + x + 1.

  Bit ordering convention: SP 800-38D uses the "big-endian-bit" convention
  where bit 0 of a byte is the MSB. When implementing the multiply on
  byte-arrays we reflect each byte's bits before/after the multiply or
  equivalently implement the GHASH bit-reversed-mult directly. We use the
  reflected representation: a 128-bit element is held as 16 bytes with
  bit 0 of byte 0 representing the leftmost (high-degree) coefficient in
  the GF(2^128) polynomial. The shift-and-XOR multiply below operates
  consistently with this convention; the resulting tag matches NIST CAVP
  vectors byte-for-byte.

Side-channel posture:
- Constant-time block encryption (inherits aes.runa CT discipline).
- Constant-time GHASH: implemented via shift-and-XOR over bit positions.
  No data-dependent table lookups, no branches on key material. Each
  multiply consumes the same number of cycles regardless of operand
  values.
- Constant-time tag compare on decrypt: uses
  secure_memory.constant_time_compare.
- Verify-then-decrypt order: on aes_gcm_open we recompute the tag and
  compare BEFORE materializing the plaintext. A tag mismatch leaves the
  output buffer untouched, defeating chosen-ciphertext oracles on tag
  failure.
- Misuse resistance: only the canonical 96-bit IV is accepted. Non-96-bit
  IVs require a GHASH-derived J0 and create a much larger surface for
  catastrophic nonce-reuse failures. Higher-level callers can apply
  HKDF or AES-SIV if they cannot guarantee 96-bit-IV uniqueness; this
  module does not silently accept the more error-prone shape.

CPU acceleration:
- We probe for PCLMULQDQ via aes.aes_supports_pclmulqdq. The probe result
  is exported through aes_gcm_pclmulqdq_available so external GHASH
  implementations can choose acceleration; the in-module GHASH uses the
  constant-time bit-by-bit reference path so that the same code services
  every architecture and the NIST CAVP KAT vectors match byte-for-byte
  unconditionally.

References:
- NIST SP 800-38D, "Recommendation for Block Cipher Modes of Operation:
  Galois/Counter Mode (GCM) and GMAC", Nov 2007.
- FIPS PUB 197 (AES).
- D. McGrew, J. Viega, "The Galois/Counter Mode of Operation (GCM)",
  May 2005.
- Intel, "Intel Carry-Less Multiplication Instruction and its Usage for
  Computing the GCM Mode", Rev 2.02, April 2014.
- Niels Ferguson, "Authentication weaknesses in GCM", 2005 (motivates
  the 96-bit-IV-only stance and the verify-then-decrypt order).
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Memory
Import "runtime/core/memory/arena.runa" as Arena
Import "compiler/frontend/import_system/crypto/aes.runa" as AES
Import "compiler/frontend/import_system/crypto/secure_memory.runa" as SecureMem

Constant AES_GCM_TAG_SIZE as Integer is 16
Constant AES_GCM_IV_SIZE as Integer is 12
Constant AES_GCM_BLOCK_SIZE as Integer is 16
Constant AES_GCM_KEY_SIZE_128 as Integer is 16
Constant AES_GCM_KEY_SIZE_192 as Integer is 24
Constant AES_GCM_KEY_SIZE_256 as Integer is 32

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Capability probe (re-exports the PCLMULQDQ flag for higher layers)
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "aes_gcm_pclmulqdq_available" returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Reports whether the runtime CPU advertises PCLMULQDQ. Higher layers
    (e.g., TLS record layer, KEM hybrid signatures) may select an
    AES-GCM implementation that uses PCLMULQDQ for the GHASH multiply.
    This module's GHASH is the constant-time bit-by-bit reference path,
    so this flag is informational only here.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Delegates to aes.aes_supports_pclmulqdq.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    ~100 cycles (CPUID).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    No secret-dependent control flow.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let v be proc aes_supports_pclmulqdq from AES
    Return v
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: GHASH: GF(2^128) multiplication with x^128 + x^7 + x^2 + x + 1 reduction.
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "gcm_block_xor" takes dst as Integer, src1 as Integer, src2 as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    XORs two 16-byte blocks into dst. Helper used by GHASH and by the
    CTR-mode encryptor.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Bytewise XOR loop of 16 bytes.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    16 byte loads × 2 + 16 byte stores. ~50 ALU ops.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Constant-time.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let i be 0
    While i is less than 16:
        Let a be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with src1, i
        Let b be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with src2, i
        Let x be a bitwise_xor b
        proc memory_set_byte from Memory with dst, i, x
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "gcm_gf128_mul" takes arena as Integer, x as Integer, y as Integer, out_block as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Constant-time multiplication in GF(2^128) per the GCM convention
    (SP 800-38D section 6.3). The reduction polynomial is
    R = x^128 + x^7 + x^2 + x + 1 (low-order bits in the GCM
    representation: byte 0 bit 7 = leading coefficient, the standard
    "left-to-right" reading specified in the spec).

    The algorithm is the textbook shift-XOR multiply: walk every bit
    of one operand; for each set bit, XOR the (possibly already shifted)
    other operand into the accumulator; shift the other operand right by
    one position with conditional XOR of the reduction polynomial when
    the lowest bit was set.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Per SP 800-38D appendix:
      Z = 0
      V = Y
      For i from 0 to 127:
        bit = (X[i/8] >> (7 - (i mod 8))) & 1       Note: i-th bit of X big-endian-bit
        Z ^= V * bit                                Note: conditional via arithmetic mask
        lsb_v = V[15] & 1                           Note: lowest bit (rightmost) of V
        V >>= 1                                     Note: shift V right by 1 (toward higher byte indices,
                                                    Note: low-bit goes out)
        V ^= R_byte_pattern * lsb_v                 Note: conditional reduction by 0xE1 in byte 0
                                                    Note: (reflected representation of 11100001 = 0x87 reversed)
      Return Z

    The reduction is applied via a 0xE1 XOR to the high byte (byte 0)
    when the bit shifted out was 1. This is the standard GCM
    bit-reflected encoding of the reduction polynomial.

    The "conditional" operations are performed via arithmetic masks
    (- of a 0/1 bit yields 0 or 0xFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFF, then AND with the
    operand). No branches on secret data.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    128 iterations × ~30 ops per iteration = ~4000 ops per multiply.
    Dominant cost of GHASH on the software path. PCLMULQDQ acceleration
    brings this to ~7 cycles per multiply but requires the operand to
    live in an XMM register; this module deliberately uses the CT
    bit-by-bit path so the NIST CAVP KAT vectors validate on every
    architecture.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Constant-time. Every iteration does the same ALU work regardless
    of operand bits. No memory accesses depend on secret bits.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let z_buf be proc arena_allocate from Arena with arena, 16
    If z_buf is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let v_buf be proc arena_allocate from Arena with arena, 16
    If v_buf is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Z = 0
    Let zi be 0
    While zi is less than 16:
        proc memory_set_byte from Memory with z_buf, zi, 0
        Set zi to zi plus 1
    End While

    Note: V = Y
    Let yi be 0
    While yi is less than 16:
        Let yb be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with y, yi
        proc memory_set_byte from Memory with v_buf, yi, yb
        Set yi to yi plus 1
    End While

    Note: Walk bits of X big-endian-bit-first
    Let bit_idx be 0
    While bit_idx is less than 128:
        Let byte_idx be bit_idx divided by 8
        Let bit_in_byte be bit_idx modulo by 8
        Let xb be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with x, byte_idx
        Let shift_amt be 7 minus bit_in_byte
        Let shifter be 1
        Let sa be 0
        While sa is less than shift_amt:
            Set shifter to shifter multiplied by 2
            Set sa to sa plus 1
        End While
        Let xbit be xb divided by shifter
        Set xbit to xbit bitwise_and 1

        Note: Conditional Z ^= V
        Let mask be 0 minus xbit
        Set mask to mask bitwise_and 255
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than 16:
            Let zb be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with z_buf, i
            Let vb be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with v_buf, i
            Let vmasked be vb bitwise_and mask
            Let zn be zb bitwise_xor vmasked
            proc memory_set_byte from Memory with z_buf, i, zn
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While

        Note: Determine lsb of V (the lowest bit of byte 15) before shifting
        Let v15 be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with v_buf, 15
        Let lsb_v be v15 bitwise_and 1
        Let red_mask be 0 minus lsb_v
        Set red_mask to red_mask bitwise_and 255

        Note: Shift V right by 1 (across the 16-byte big-endian representation,
        Note: meaning the bit that was bit 0 of byte k moves to bit 7 of byte k+1,
        Note: bit 0 of byte 15 falls off, and bit 7 of byte 0 becomes 0)
        Let j be 15
        While j is greater than 0:
            Let cur be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with v_buf, j
            Let prev be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with v_buf, j minus 1
            Let cur_shifted be cur divided by 2
            Let prev_lsb be prev bitwise_and 1
            Let prev_lsb_in_msb be prev_lsb multiplied by 128
            Let new_byte be cur_shifted bitwise_or prev_lsb_in_msb
            Set new_byte to new_byte bitwise_and 255
            proc memory_set_byte from Memory with v_buf, j, new_byte
            Set j to j minus 1
        End While
        Let v0 be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with v_buf, 0
        Let v0_shifted be v0 divided by 2
        Set v0_shifted to v0_shifted bitwise_and 255
        proc memory_set_byte from Memory with v_buf, 0, v0_shifted

        Note: Conditional reduction: V[0] ^= (0xE1 if lsb_v else 0)
        Let v0_after be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with v_buf, 0
        Let red_byte be 225 bitwise_and red_mask
        Let v0_red be v0_after bitwise_xor red_byte
        proc memory_set_byte from Memory with v_buf, 0, v0_red

        Set bit_idx to bit_idx plus 1
    End While

    Note: Copy Z into out_block
    Let ok be 0
    While ok is less than 16:
        Let zfinal be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with z_buf, ok
        proc memory_set_byte from Memory with out_block, ok, zfinal
        Set ok to ok plus 1
    End While
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "gcm_ghash" takes arena as Integer, h_key as Integer, data as Integer, data_len as Integer, y_in_out as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    GHASH iterative update: for each 16-byte block X_i in data,
    y = (y XOR X_i) * H. data_len is the total byte length of data,
    which must be a multiple of 16 (caller responsibility - the AEAD
    builds a zero-padded buffer to meet this requirement).
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Loop block-by-block:
      For each block:
        XOR data[i*16..i*16+16] into y_in_out.
        y_in_out = gcm_gf128_mul(y_in_out, h_key).
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(data_len) blocks × one gf128_mul each. The multiply dominates;
    GHASH cost is ~32 µs/KB on this software path. With PCLMULQDQ
    that drops to ~0.2 µs/KB.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Constant-time per block.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let num_blocks be data_len divided by 16
    Let blk be 0
    While blk is less than num_blocks:
        Let base be blk multiplied by 16
        Let xi be 0
        While xi is less than 16:
            Let yb be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with y_in_out, xi
            Let db be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with data, base plus xi
            Let xored be yb bitwise_xor db
            proc memory_set_byte from Memory with y_in_out, xi, xored
            Set xi to xi plus 1
        End While
        Let tmp be proc arena_allocate from Arena with arena, 16
        If tmp is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Let mrc be proc gcm_gf128_mul with arena, y_in_out, h_key, tmp
        If mrc is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Let ti be 0
        While ti is less than 16:
            Let tb be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with tmp, ti
            proc memory_set_byte from Memory with y_in_out, ti, tb
            Set ti to ti plus 1
        End While
        Set blk to blk plus 1
    End While
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: GCM counter increment (rightmost 32 bits, modulo 2^32)
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "gcm_inc32" takes block as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Increments the rightmost 32 bits of a 16-byte counter block (big
    endian) modulo 2^32 per SP 800-38D section 6.2. The leftmost 96
    bits (the IV portion) are unchanged.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Treat block[12..16] as a 32-bit big-endian counter. Increment with
    wraparound at 2^32.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    Constant time. A few byte ops.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    No secret-dependent control flow.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let b12 be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with block, 12
    Let b13 be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with block, 13
    Let b14 be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with block, 14
    Let b15 be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with block, 15
    Let ctr be b12 multiplied by 16777216
    Set ctr to ctr plus b13 multiplied by 65536
    Set ctr to ctr plus b14 multiplied by 256
    Set ctr to ctr plus b15
    Set ctr to ctr plus 1
    Set ctr to ctr bitwise_and 4294967295
    Let n12 be ctr divided by 16777216
    Set n12 to n12 bitwise_and 255
    Let n13 be ctr divided by 65536
    Set n13 to n13 bitwise_and 255
    Let n14 be ctr divided by 256
    Set n14 to n14 bitwise_and 255
    Let n15 be ctr bitwise_and 255
    proc memory_set_byte from Memory with block, 12, n12
    proc memory_set_byte from Memory with block, 13, n13
    proc memory_set_byte from Memory with block, 14, n14
    proc memory_set_byte from Memory with block, 15, n15
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Internal: schedule-size dispatch
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "gcm_schedule_size_for_key_len" takes key_len as Integer returns Integer:
    If key_len is equal to AES_GCM_KEY_SIZE_128:
        Return 176
    End If
    If key_len is equal to AES_GCM_KEY_SIZE_192:
        Return 208
    End If
    If key_len is equal to AES_GCM_KEY_SIZE_256:
        Return 240
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "gcm_expand_schedule" takes arena as Integer, key as Integer, key_len as Integer, schedule as Integer returns Integer:
    If key_len is equal to AES_GCM_KEY_SIZE_128:
        Return proc aes128_key_expand from AES with arena, key, schedule
    End If
    If key_len is equal to AES_GCM_KEY_SIZE_192:
        Return proc aes192_key_expand from AES with arena, key, schedule
    End If
    If key_len is equal to AES_GCM_KEY_SIZE_256:
        Return proc aes256_key_expand from AES with arena, key, schedule
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Compute H = E_K(0^128), the GHASH subkey
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "gcm_compute_h" takes arena as Integer, schedule as Integer, schedule_size as Integer, h_out as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    The GHASH subkey H is defined as the AES-encryption of the
    all-zeros block under K.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Allocate a 16-byte zero buffer; AES-encrypt it; the output is H.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    One AES block encrypt. Computed once per AEAD invocation.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    H is key-derived (effectively a per-key MAC key). Caller must
    avoid leaking H via side channels; this proc does not store H
    in any external state.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let zero_block be proc arena_allocate from Arena with arena, 16
    If zero_block is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let zi be 0
    While zi is less than 16:
        proc memory_set_byte from Memory with zero_block, zi, 0
        Set zi to zi plus 1
    End While
    Return proc aes_encrypt_block from AES with arena, schedule, schedule_size, zero_block, h_out
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: CTR-mode encrypt: in-place XOR with E_K(counter), counter increments
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "gcm_ctr_encrypt" takes arena as Integer, schedule as Integer, schedule_size as Integer, counter_block as Integer, input as Integer, input_len as Integer, output as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    CTR-mode encryption used by GCM: encrypt the counter, XOR with the
    plaintext (or ciphertext - the operation is involutive), increment
    the rightmost 32 bits of the counter modulo 2^32, repeat.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    For each block:
      ks = AES_encrypt(counter_block)
      output[block] = input[block] XOR ks[0..min(remaining, 16)]
      inc32(counter_block)
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    One AES block encrypt + 16 XORs per 16 bytes of data.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Constant-time.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let ks_buf be proc arena_allocate from Arena with arena, 16
    If ks_buf is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let processed be 0
    While processed is less than input_len:
        Let erc be proc aes_encrypt_block from AES with arena, schedule, schedule_size, counter_block, ks_buf
        If erc is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Let remaining be input_len minus processed
        Let chunk be remaining
        If chunk is greater than 16:
            Set chunk to 16
        End If
        Let ci be 0
        While ci is less than chunk:
            Let ib be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with input, processed plus ci
            Let kb be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with ks_buf, ci
            Let ob be ib bitwise_xor kb
            proc memory_set_byte from Memory with output, processed plus ci, ob
            Set ci to ci plus 1
        End While
        proc gcm_inc32 with counter_block
        Set processed to processed plus chunk
    End While
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Build the GHASH input: AAD || pad to 16 || CT || pad to 16 || len(A)_64 || len(C)_64
Note: All length bit-counts are encoded big-endian per SP 800-38D.
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "gcm_compute_tag" takes arena as Integer, h_key as Integer, aad as Integer, aad_len as Integer, ct as Integer, ct_len as Integer, tag_state as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Computes the raw GHASH output S = GHASH_H(A || pad || C || pad || lenA_bits_be64
    || lenC_bits_be64). The caller XORs this with E_K(J0) to form the
    final tag.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. Zero the running tag_state buffer.
    2. Process AAD blocks (full 16-byte blocks).
    3. Process trailing partial AAD block padded with zeros to 16 bytes.
    4. Process CT blocks similarly.
    5. Process the length block: 8 bytes big-endian for aad_len*8, then
       8 bytes big-endian for ct_len*8.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(aad_len + ct_len + 16) bytes processed × one gf128_mul per
    16-byte block. The mul dominates.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Constant-time.
    @End Security_Scope

    Note: Zero tag_state
    Let zi be 0
    While zi is less than 16:
        proc memory_set_byte from Memory with tag_state, zi, 0
        Set zi to zi plus 1
    End While

    Note: Process AAD full blocks
    Let aad_full_blocks be aad_len divided by 16
    Let aad_full_bytes be aad_full_blocks multiplied by 16
    If aad_full_bytes is greater than 0:
        Let rc1 be proc gcm_ghash with arena, h_key, aad, aad_full_bytes, tag_state
        If rc1 is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
    End If

    Note: AAD trailing partial block
    Let aad_remainder be aad_len minus aad_full_bytes
    If aad_remainder is greater than 0:
        Let pad_block be proc arena_allocate from Arena with arena, 16
        If pad_block is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Let pi be 0
        While pi is less than 16:
            proc memory_set_byte from Memory with pad_block, pi, 0
            Set pi to pi plus 1
        End While
        Let pj be 0
        While pj is less than aad_remainder:
            Let ab be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with aad, aad_full_bytes plus pj
            proc memory_set_byte from Memory with pad_block, pj, ab
            Set pj to pj plus 1
        End While
        Let rc2 be proc gcm_ghash with arena, h_key, pad_block, 16, tag_state
        If rc2 is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
    End If

    Note: Process CT full blocks
    Let ct_full_blocks be ct_len divided by 16
    Let ct_full_bytes be ct_full_blocks multiplied by 16
    If ct_full_bytes is greater than 0:
        Let rc3 be proc gcm_ghash with arena, h_key, ct, ct_full_bytes, tag_state
        If rc3 is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
    End If

    Note: CT trailing partial block
    Let ct_remainder be ct_len minus ct_full_bytes
    If ct_remainder is greater than 0:
        Let pad_block2 be proc arena_allocate from Arena with arena, 16
        If pad_block2 is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Let p2i be 0
        While p2i is less than 16:
            proc memory_set_byte from Memory with pad_block2, p2i, 0
            Set p2i to p2i plus 1
        End While
        Let p2j be 0
        While p2j is less than ct_remainder:
            Let cb be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with ct, ct_full_bytes plus p2j
            proc memory_set_byte from Memory with pad_block2, p2j, cb
            Set p2j to p2j plus 1
        End While
        Let rc4 be proc gcm_ghash with arena, h_key, pad_block2, 16, tag_state
        If rc4 is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
    End If

    Note: Length block: 8 bytes BE for aad_len*8, then 8 bytes BE for ct_len*8
    Let len_block be proc arena_allocate from Arena with arena, 16
    If len_block is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let aad_bits be aad_len multiplied by 8
    Let ct_bits be ct_len multiplied by 8

    Note: aad_bits big-endian into len_block[0..8]
    Let a7 be aad_bits bitwise_and 255
    Let a6 be aad_bits divided by 256
    Set a6 to a6 bitwise_and 255
    Let a5 be aad_bits divided by 65536
    Set a5 to a5 bitwise_and 255
    Let a4 be aad_bits divided by 16777216
    Set a4 to a4 bitwise_and 255
    Let a3 be aad_bits divided by 4294967296
    Set a3 to a3 bitwise_and 255
    Let a2 be aad_bits divided by 1099511627776
    Set a2 to a2 bitwise_and 255
    Let a1 be aad_bits divided by 281474976710656
    Set a1 to a1 bitwise_and 255
    Let a0 be aad_bits divided by 72057594037927936
    Set a0 to a0 bitwise_and 255
    proc memory_set_byte from Memory with len_block, 0, a0
    proc memory_set_byte from Memory with len_block, 1, a1
    proc memory_set_byte from Memory with len_block, 2, a2
    proc memory_set_byte from Memory with len_block, 3, a3
    proc memory_set_byte from Memory with len_block, 4, a4
    proc memory_set_byte from Memory with len_block, 5, a5
    proc memory_set_byte from Memory with len_block, 6, a6
    proc memory_set_byte from Memory with len_block, 7, a7

    Note: ct_bits big-endian into len_block[8..16]
    Let c7 be ct_bits bitwise_and 255
    Let c6 be ct_bits divided by 256
    Set c6 to c6 bitwise_and 255
    Let c5 be ct_bits divided by 65536
    Set c5 to c5 bitwise_and 255
    Let c4 be ct_bits divided by 16777216
    Set c4 to c4 bitwise_and 255
    Let c3 be ct_bits divided by 4294967296
    Set c3 to c3 bitwise_and 255
    Let c2 be ct_bits divided by 1099511627776
    Set c2 to c2 bitwise_and 255
    Let c1 be ct_bits divided by 281474976710656
    Set c1 to c1 bitwise_and 255
    Let c0 be ct_bits divided by 72057594037927936
    Set c0 to c0 bitwise_and 255
    proc memory_set_byte from Memory with len_block, 8, c0
    proc memory_set_byte from Memory with len_block, 9, c1
    proc memory_set_byte from Memory with len_block, 10, c2
    proc memory_set_byte from Memory with len_block, 11, c3
    proc memory_set_byte from Memory with len_block, 12, c4
    proc memory_set_byte from Memory with len_block, 13, c5
    proc memory_set_byte from Memory with len_block, 14, c6
    proc memory_set_byte from Memory with len_block, 15, c7

    Let rc5 be proc gcm_ghash with arena, h_key, len_block, 16, tag_state
    If rc5 is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: AEAD seal: encrypt + authenticate
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "aes_gcm_seal" takes arena as Integer, key as Integer, key_len as Integer, iv_12 as Integer, aad as Integer, aad_len as Integer, plaintext as Integer, pt_len as Integer, ciphertext_out as Integer, tag_out as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    AES-GCM seal per SP 800-38D. Encrypts the plaintext under (K, IV)
    with CTR mode and produces a 16-byte authentication tag covering
    AAD and ciphertext.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. Validate inputs:
       - key_len in {16, 24, 32}
       - iv_12 non-null (always 12 bytes per the 96-bit-IV-only stance)
       - lengths non-negative; AAD/PT pointers consistent with lengths.
    2. Expand the AES key schedule (176/208/240 bytes).
    3. Compute H = E_K(0^128).
    4. Build J0 = IV || 0x00000001 (96-bit IV plus 32-bit counter=1).
    5. Compute E_K(J0) into a 16-byte buffer for later XOR with GHASH.
    6. Initialize CTR counter to J0 with the rightmost 32 bits = 2 (inc32(J0)).
    7. CTR-encrypt plaintext into ciphertext_out.
    8. Compute S = GHASH_H(A || pad || C || pad || len(A) || len(C)).
    9. Tag = S XOR E_K(J0).
    10. Wipe H, the GHASH state, and the J0-encrypted block.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    Dominant costs:
    - One AES key schedule (one-shot).
    - One AES block for H computation.
    - One AES block for E_K(J0).
    - pt_len/16 AES blocks for CTR.
    - (aad_len + pt_len + 16) / 16 GF(2^128) multiplies for GHASH.
    On the software path, GHASH dominates for messages >100 bytes.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Constant-time throughout.

    NEVER reuse a (key, IV) pair across distinct plaintexts. GCM nonce
    reuse catastrophically exposes the GHASH subkey H, allowing
    arbitrary tag forgery in addition to leaking plaintext XOR
    plaintext between the colliding messages. Callers MUST ensure
    uniqueness of IVs per key, e.g., via a deterministic 96-bit
    counter or via 96 bits of uniformly-random data with sufficient
    key rotation per RFC 5116.

    The 96-bit-IV-only stance is a deliberate misuse-resistance choice.
    SP 800-38D permits other IV sizes but they require GHASH-based J0
    derivation which is fragile under truncation and length-extension
    confusion. Callers needing 64-bit nonces or longer should use a
    KDF (e.g., HKDF) to derive a fresh 96-bit IV per message.

    References:
    - SP 800-38D section 8.2.1.
    - Ferguson, "Authentication weaknesses in GCM", 2005.
    @End Security_Scope

    If arena is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If key is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If iv_12 is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If tag_out is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If pt_len is less than 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If aad_len is less than 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If plaintext is equal to 0:
        If pt_len is greater than 0:
            Return 0
        End If
    End If
    If ciphertext_out is equal to 0:
        If pt_len is greater than 0:
            Return 0
        End If
    End If
    If aad is equal to 0:
        If aad_len is greater than 0:
            Return 0
        End If
    End If

    Let schedule_size be proc gcm_schedule_size_for_key_len with key_len
    If schedule_size is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: ---- Expand key schedule ----
    Let schedule be proc arena_allocate from Arena with arena, schedule_size
    If schedule is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let kx_rc be proc gcm_expand_schedule with arena, key, key_len, schedule
    If kx_rc is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: ---- Compute H = E_K(0^128) ----
    Let h_key be proc arena_allocate from Arena with arena, 16
    If h_key is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let h_rc be proc gcm_compute_h with arena, schedule, schedule_size, h_key
    If h_rc is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: ---- Build J0 = IV || 00000001 ----
    Let j0 be proc arena_allocate from Arena with arena, 16
    If j0 is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let ji be 0
    While ji is less than 12:
        Let iv_byte be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with iv_12, ji
        proc memory_set_byte from Memory with j0, ji, iv_byte
        Set ji to ji plus 1
    End While
    proc memory_set_byte from Memory with j0, 12, 0
    proc memory_set_byte from Memory with j0, 13, 0
    proc memory_set_byte from Memory with j0, 14, 0
    proc memory_set_byte from Memory with j0, 15, 1

    Note: ---- E_K(J0) for final tag XOR ----
    Let ekj0 be proc arena_allocate from Arena with arena, 16
    If ekj0 is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let e_rc be proc aes_encrypt_block from AES with arena, schedule, schedule_size, j0, ekj0
    If e_rc is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: ---- CTR counter starts at inc32(J0) ----
    Let counter_block be proc arena_allocate from Arena with arena, 16
    If counter_block is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let cbi be 0
    While cbi is less than 16:
        Let jb be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with j0, cbi
        proc memory_set_byte from Memory with counter_block, cbi, jb
        Set cbi to cbi plus 1
    End While
    proc gcm_inc32 with counter_block

    Note: ---- CTR encrypt plaintext -> ciphertext_out ----
    If pt_len is greater than 0:
        Let ctr_rc be proc gcm_ctr_encrypt with arena, schedule, schedule_size, counter_block, plaintext, pt_len, ciphertext_out
        If ctr_rc is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
    End If

    Note: ---- GHASH over (AAD, CT, lengths) ----
    Let tag_state be proc arena_allocate from Arena with arena, 16
    If tag_state is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let gh_rc be proc gcm_compute_tag with arena, h_key, aad, aad_len, ciphertext_out, pt_len, tag_state
    If gh_rc is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: ---- Tag = tag_state XOR ekj0 ----
    Let ti be 0
    While ti is less than 16:
        Let sb be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with tag_state, ti
        Let eb be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with ekj0, ti
        Let tb be sb bitwise_xor eb
        proc memory_set_byte from Memory with tag_out, ti, tb
        Set ti to ti plus 1
    End While

    Note: ---- Wipe key-derived intermediates ----
    proc secure_zero from SecureMem with h_key, 16
    proc secure_zero from SecureMem with ekj0, 16
    proc secure_zero from SecureMem with tag_state, 16
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: AEAD open: verify tag (constant-time) then decrypt
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "aes_gcm_open" takes arena as Integer, key as Integer, key_len as Integer, iv_12 as Integer, aad as Integer, aad_len as Integer, ciphertext as Integer, ct_len as Integer, tag as Integer, plaintext_out as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    AES-GCM open per SP 800-38D section 7.2. Recomputes the tag over
    (AAD, ciphertext) and constant-time-compares against the supplied
    tag; if they match, decrypts the ciphertext into plaintext_out and
    returns 1, otherwise leaves plaintext_out untouched and returns 0.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. Validate inputs (mirror of seal).
    2. Expand schedule, compute H, build J0, compute E_K(J0).
    3. Compute tag_state over (AAD, CT, lengths) via GHASH.
    4. Recomputed_tag = tag_state XOR E_K(J0).
    5. constant_time_compare recomputed_tag against supplied tag.
    6. If unequal, wipe and return 0.
    7. If equal, CTR-decrypt ciphertext into plaintext_out and return 1.
    8. Wipe key-derived material in both paths.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    Same cost profile as seal.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Hardened against:
    - Tag-bit timing oracles (constant_time_compare).
    - Chosen-ciphertext oracles on tag failure (verify before decrypt;
      plaintext_out is not written when the tag fails).
    - GHASH-key recovery via nonce reuse on a SINGLE message (the
      forward-secrecy of the AEAD does not protect against multi-message
      nonce reuse; the caller MUST avoid that).

    Out of scope: protocol-level replay (caller layer).
    @End Security_Scope

    If arena is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If key is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If iv_12 is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If tag is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If ct_len is less than 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If aad_len is less than 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If ciphertext is equal to 0:
        If ct_len is greater than 0:
            Return 0
        End If
    End If
    If plaintext_out is equal to 0:
        If ct_len is greater than 0:
            Return 0
        End If
    End If
    If aad is equal to 0:
        If aad_len is greater than 0:
            Return 0
        End If
    End If

    Let schedule_size be proc gcm_schedule_size_for_key_len with key_len
    If schedule_size is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let schedule be proc arena_allocate from Arena with arena, schedule_size
    If schedule is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let kx_rc be proc gcm_expand_schedule with arena, key, key_len, schedule
    If kx_rc is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let h_key be proc arena_allocate from Arena with arena, 16
    If h_key is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let h_rc be proc gcm_compute_h with arena, schedule, schedule_size, h_key
    If h_rc is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let j0 be proc arena_allocate from Arena with arena, 16
    If j0 is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let ji be 0
    While ji is less than 12:
        Let iv_byte be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with iv_12, ji
        proc memory_set_byte from Memory with j0, ji, iv_byte
        Set ji to ji plus 1
    End While
    proc memory_set_byte from Memory with j0, 12, 0
    proc memory_set_byte from Memory with j0, 13, 0
    proc memory_set_byte from Memory with j0, 14, 0
    proc memory_set_byte from Memory with j0, 15, 1

    Let ekj0 be proc arena_allocate from Arena with arena, 16
    If ekj0 is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let e_rc be proc aes_encrypt_block from AES with arena, schedule, schedule_size, j0, ekj0
    If e_rc is equal to 0:
        proc secure_zero from SecureMem with h_key, 16
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: GHASH over (AAD, received CT, lengths) FIRST (verify before decrypt)
    Let tag_state be proc arena_allocate from Arena with arena, 16
    If tag_state is equal to 0:
        proc secure_zero from SecureMem with h_key, 16
        proc secure_zero from SecureMem with ekj0, 16
        Return 0
    End If
    Let gh_rc be proc gcm_compute_tag with arena, h_key, aad, aad_len, ciphertext, ct_len, tag_state
    If gh_rc is equal to 0:
        proc secure_zero from SecureMem with h_key, 16
        proc secure_zero from SecureMem with ekj0, 16
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Recomputed tag = tag_state XOR ekj0
    Let recomputed be proc arena_allocate from Arena with arena, 16
    If recomputed is equal to 0:
        proc secure_zero from SecureMem with h_key, 16
        proc secure_zero from SecureMem with ekj0, 16
        proc secure_zero from SecureMem with tag_state, 16
        Return 0
    End If
    Let ti be 0
    While ti is less than 16:
        Let sb be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with tag_state, ti
        Let eb be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with ekj0, ti
        Let rb be sb bitwise_xor eb
        proc memory_set_byte from Memory with recomputed, ti, rb
        Set ti to ti plus 1
    End While

    Note: Constant-time tag compare
    Let eq be proc constant_time_compare from SecureMem with recomputed, tag, 16

    Note: Wipe regardless of outcome
    proc secure_zero from SecureMem with h_key, 16
    proc secure_zero from SecureMem with tag_state, 16
    proc secure_zero from SecureMem with recomputed, 16

    If eq is equal to 0:
        proc secure_zero from SecureMem with ekj0, 16
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Tag valid: decrypt
    If ct_len is greater than 0:
        Let counter_block be proc arena_allocate from Arena with arena, 16
        If counter_block is equal to 0:
            proc secure_zero from SecureMem with ekj0, 16
            Return 0
        End If
        Let cbi be 0
        While cbi is less than 16:
            Let jb be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with j0, cbi
            proc memory_set_byte from Memory with counter_block, cbi, jb
            Set cbi to cbi plus 1
        End While
        proc gcm_inc32 with counter_block
        Let ctr_rc be proc gcm_ctr_encrypt with arena, schedule, schedule_size, counter_block, ciphertext, ct_len, plaintext_out
        If ctr_rc is equal to 0:
            proc secure_zero from SecureMem with ekj0, 16
            Return 0
        End If
    End If

    proc secure_zero from SecureMem with ekj0, 16
    Return 1
End Process
